  "text": "A multimodality mapping study based on 34 patients (overall 317 LNs were detected) showed that PLND for PCa should include not only the external and obturator regions including the portions medial and lateral to the internal iliac vessels, but also the common iliac LNs at least up to the ureteral crossing, thus removing approximately 75% of all nodes that might potentially harbour metastasis [CITATION_1] .",
